data.description: Don't miss out on this Old Colorado City duplex! Rare find in a prime area of Old Colorado City with Pikes Peak views and open area across the street! This charming rancher duplex has an excellent rental history. Keep one unit rented and occupy the other or cash flow the building with tenants in both sides of the property. One unit is occupied and rent in this unit is below market, which means an upside in rents for your buyers. This property has undergone recent renovations, including a newer roof, newer exterior paint, and current foundation and drainage mitigation by a licensed structural engineer and licensed contractors. Please see the attached documents to review the engineering report. Unit A (occupied) features a jetted tub, gas stove, wainscot in the bathroom, ceiling fans, six-panel doors, hardwood floors and a storage shed. Unit B (vacant) includes upgrades, such as wood floors, new interior paint, and recently refurbished floors. No problems with off-street parking here. This property has a large area parking and fenced rear yard space for tenants.
